The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Tata Balanced Fund has declared a dividend of 30 per cent and the record date for the payout is January 12. Also, a 30 per cent dividend has been declared under the income plan of Canexpo with the record date being January 20. 

 Magnum Balanced Fund has declared a dividend of 20 per cent and the record date is January 19. Birla Sun Life Mutual Fund has also declared the record dates for dividend payout under Birla MNC Fund and Birla Mid-cap Fund as January 14 and January 28, respectively. 

 JM Mutual Fund has revised the entry load in the equity, balanced, basic, auto and healthcare sector funds. An entry load of 2.25 per cent would be charged for all investments up to Rs 50 lakh.

 Reliance Mutual has introduced Systematic Transfer Plan in 13 of its schemes ? growth, vision, income, liquid, medium term, short term, banking, gilt securities, monthly income plan, diversified power sector, pharma, floating rate and media and entertainment funds.

 The minimum application amount for Birla Floating Rate Fund has been reduced to Rs 5,000.




